'''''Brewer's Dictionary of Irish Phrase and Fable''''' ({{ISBN|0-304-36334-0}}) was created by Jo O'Donoghue and Sean McMahon for the ''[[Brewer's Dictionary of Phrase and Fable]]'' series of books. It contains over five thousand entries regarding various subjects about [[Ireland]] and its [[saying]]s, [[mythology|myths]], [[legend]]s and [[fable]]s.

