{{Infobox court case | name = Walsh v Kerr | court = [[Court of Appeal of New Zealand]] | date_filed = | image = Coat of arms of New Zealand.svg | date decided = 7 June 1989 | full name = Walsh v Kerr | citations = [1989] 1 NZLR 490 | judges = [[Robin Brunskill Cooke|Cooke P]], [[Edward Somers|Somers J]], [[Michael Hardie Boys|Hardie Boys J]] | prior actions = | subsequent actions = | opinions = | transcripts = | Keywords = }} '''Walsh v Kerr''' [1989] 1 NZLR 490 is a cited case in New Zealand regarding the remedy of damages for breach of [[contract]].<ref name="Chetwin, Graw, Tiong">{{cite book |title=An introduction to the Law of Contract in New Zealand |edition=4th |last1=Chetwin |first1=Maree |last2=Graw |first2=Stephen |last3=Tiong |first3=Raymond |publisher=Thomson Brookers |ISBN=0-86472-555-8 |year=2006 |page={{page needed|date=January 2014}}}}</ref><ref name="Walker">{{cite book |title=Butterworths Student Companion Contract |edition=4th |last1=Walker |first1=Campbell |publisher=LexisNexis |ISBN=0-408-71770-X|year=2004 |page=233}}</ref>
