{{Use British English|date=January 2017}}
'''William of Lindholme''' is a legendary British giant, who lived in the [[Fen|Fenland]] town of [[Lindholme, South Yorkshire]].

He is held to have thrown the "thumb stone" and "little-finger stone" from Lindholme to [[Wroot]], some three miles distant.<ref>{{Cite book|title=Ghosts and Legends of Lincolnshire and the Fen County|author=Polly Howat|isbn=978-1-85306-192-9|date=1992}}</ref>

